    <text id="B2040T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Manly asks Cook for details about the state of schools in Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Lieutenant">Lieut</abbr> Geo. T. Cook <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Superintendent">Asst. Sup</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-11-10"><abbr expan="November">Nov.</abbr> 10 '66</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Lieutenant">Lieut</abbr>:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to inquire in regard to Freedmen's schools in Staunton. How may
                    teachers, how many scholars, how are they accomodated in respect to school
                    rooms? If repairs <hi rend="underline">are</hi> necessary, what is the smallest
                    sum that will <add hand="h1" place="inline">meet</add> the demand. If additional
                    room is required, cannot a room be rented rather than to build? An immediate
                    reply is very desirable. Write directly to me.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very <abbr expan="Respectfully">Resp'y</abbr> yours<lb/>By order of
                            <abbr expan="General">Gen.</abbr> O. Brown <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>R.M. Manly<lb/><abbr expan="Superintendent of">Supt</abbr>
                    Education</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
